<emphasis id="B95E0B5E37511B71FF6E4111FED3E85F" bold="true" box="[192,346,1857,1881]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Discussion.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBBAABD37511B71FEF14112FD6AE85C" author="Rodrigues, J. M. D. S. &amp; J. R. M. Mermudes" box="[351,739,1858,1882]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" pagination="44 - 48" refId="ref13056" refString="Rodrigues, J. M. D. S., and J. R. M. Mermudes. 2011. A new species of Peritrox Bates, with a revised key for the genus (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae). Zootaxa 3000: 44 - 48." type="journal article" year="2011">Rodrigues and Mermudes (2011)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C2AACCF37511B71FCCE4112FBBFE85C" authorityName="Rodrigues and Mermudes" authorityYear="2011" box="[864,1078,1858,1882]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Peritrox" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insulatus">
<emphasis id="B95E0B5E37511B71FCCE4112FBBFE85C" box="[864,1078,1858,1882]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Peritrox insulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a single female specimen collected on “ 
<collectingCountry id="F33D97DC37511B71FECA4132FE1FE87C" box="[356,406,1890,1914]" name="Iceland" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Ilha</collectingCountry>
Grande,” 
<collectingRegion id="49EE19AE37511B71FDBA4132FD43E87C" box="[532,714,1890,1914]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33D97DC37511B71FD794132FCAFE87C" box="[727,806,1890,1914]" name="Brazil" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Nearns et al. (2011) provided color photographs of 
<specimenCount id="9D2C1CC537571B77FF6E4692FEB4EFDC" box="[192,317,194,218]" pageId="20" pageNumber="19" type="generic">three type</specimenCount>
specimens of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C2AACCF37571B77FDCA4692FD4FEFDF" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1865" box="[612,710,194,217]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Peritrox" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95E0B5E37571B77FDCA4692FD4FEFDF" box="[612,710,194,217]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="19">Peritrox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on examination of the 
<typeStatus id="549169EE37571B77FB994692FB29EFDC" box="[1079,1184,194,218]" pageId="20" pageNumber="19">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen of the type species of the genus (
<taxonomicName id="4C2AACCF37571B77FE6E46B2FCC9EFFF" authority="Bates, 1865" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1865" box="[448,832,225,250]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Peritrox" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="denticollis">
<emphasis id="B95E0B5E37571B77FE6E46B2FD2EEFFC" box="[448,679,226,250]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="19">Peritrox denticollis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBBAABD37571B77FD0046B2FCC9EFFF" author="Bates, H. W." box="[686,832,225,249]" pageId="20" pageNumber="19" pagination="308 - 314" refId="ref12078" refString="Bates, H. W. 1865. Contributions to an insect fauna of the Amazon Valley. Coleoptera: Longicornes. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History 3 (15): 213 - 225, 382 - 394; 3 (16): 101 - 113, 167 - 182, 308 - 314." type="journal article" year="1865">Bates, 1865</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; deposited at the MNHN); and photographs of the type specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2AACCF37571B77FE374752FC0EEE1C" authority="Aurivillius, 1920" authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1920" box="[409,903,258,282]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Peritrox" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigromaculata">
<emphasis id="B95E0B5E37571B77FE374752FD3DEE1C" box="[409,692,258,282]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="19">Peritrox nigromaculata</emphasis>
Aurivillius, 1920
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="4C2AACCF37571B77FC3F4752FAE1EE1F" authority="Dillon and Dillon, 1945" authorityName="Dillon and Dillon" authorityYear="1945" box="[913,1384,257,282]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Peritrox" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perbra">
<emphasis id="B95E0B5E37571B77FC3F4752FBC1EE1C" box="[913,1096,258,282]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="19">Peritrox perbra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBBAABD37571B77FBE04752FAE1EE1F" author="Dillon, L. S. &amp; E. S. Dillon" box="[1102,1384,257,282]" pageId="20" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 186" refId="ref12203" refString="Dillon, L. S., and E. S. Dillon. 1945. The tribe Onciderini (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) Part I. Reading, Scientific Publications, Reading Public Museum and Art Gallery, Number 5: 1 - 186." type="book chapter" year="1945">Dillon and Dillon, 1945</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2AACCF37571B77FF6E4772FD57EE3F" authority="Dillon and Dillon, 1945" authorityName="Dillon and Dillon" authorityYear="1945" box="[192,734,289,314]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Peritrox" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vermiculatus">
<emphasis id="B95E0B5E37571B77FF6E4772FE4AEE3C" box="[192,451,290,314]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="19">Peritrox vermiculatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBBAABD37571B77FE664772FD57EE3F" author="Dillon, L. S. &amp; E. S. Dillon" box="[456,734,289,314]" pageId="20" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 186" refId="ref12203" refString="Dillon, L. S., and E. S. Dillon. 1945. The tribe Onciderini (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) Part I. Reading, Scientific Publications, Reading Public Museum and Art Gallery, Number 5: 1 - 186." type="book chapter" year="1945">Dillon and Dillon, 1945</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C2AACCF37571B77FCCC4772FC4AEE3F" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1865" box="[866,963,290,313]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Peritrox" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95E0B5E37571B77FCCC4772FC4AEE3F" box="[866,963,290,313]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="19">Peritrox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses the following characters: eyes large, oblong; frons elongate, about as wide as 1 1/2 lower eye lobe widths; genae distinctly shorter than lower eye lobes, about 1/3 as tall; antennal tubercles armed with short, blunt horn; antennal tubercles narrowly separated, contiguous at base; scape gradually expanded to apex (e.g. 
<figureCitation id="1311CBC937571B77FB3A47D2FB53EE9C" box="[1172,1242,386,410]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="8.[233,317,1837,1859]" captionTargetBox="[233,1400,192,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-36@8.[233,1400,192,1821]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 2. Peritrox marcelae, sp. nov. a) Holotype male, dorsal habitus. b) Allotype female, dorsal habitus." pageId="20" pageNumber="19">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
a-d).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF5587C437501B70FE9B4084FC1FE87D" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" startId="19.[309,393,1748,1770]" targetBox="[311,1325,193,1736]" targetPageId="19">
